inputs.name: Pivot Sensitivity Presets
inputs.tooltip: Select the sensitivity of the breakout detection, while 'Sensitive' will catch most breakouts, 'Less Sensitive' has some degree of sensitivity and catches larger swings. 'Manual' will allow you to modify the MIN/MAX pivot length in 'PIVOT AUTO LENGTH SETTINGS (MANUAL)' below.

inputs.name: MIN Pivot Length
inputs.tooltip:
Works only when 'Pivot Sensitivity Presets' is set to 'Manual'.
Sets the minimum pivot length PPA can use.
The LOWER the value is, the more sensitive it is (lowest is 1), and the HIGHER the value is, the less sensitive it is (highest 7).
[Note: 'MIN Pivot Length' must be less or equal to 'MAX Pivot Length']

inputs.name: MAX Pivot Length
inputs.tooltip:
Works only when 'Pivot Sensitivity Presets' is set to 'Manual'.
Sets the maximum pivot length PPA can use.
The HIGHER the value is, the less sensitive it is (highest is 7), while the LOWER the value is, the less sensitive it is (lowest is 1).
[Note: 'MAX Pivot Length' must be larger or equal to 'MIN Pivot Length']

inputs.name: OTC NoiseFilter strength (Main signals only)
inputs.tooltip:
Filter false breakouts only for the MAIN (labels) signal. OTC NoiseFilter is based on various variables to confirm pivot breaks out like candle patterns, volume, and such.
'Normal' is set to an average amount of filtering, compared to 'Strong' which has more strict settings.
When OTC NoiseFilter detects weak pivot breakout PPA WON'T trigger Buy or Sell signals while selecting 'None' WILL trigger Buy or Sell signals for any pivot breakout.

inputs.name: OTC NoiseFilter strength (Mini signals only)
inputs.tooltip:
Filter false breakouts only for the MINI (small triangles) signal. OTC NoiseFilter is based on various variables to confirm pivot breaks out like candle patterns, volume, and such.
'Normal' is set to an average amount of filtering, compared to 'Strong' which has more strict settings.
When OTC NoiseFilter detects weak pivot breakout PPA WON'T trigger Buy or Sell signals while selecting 'None' WILL trigger Buy or Sell signals for any pivot breakout.

inputs.name: Volume filter for Mini signals only (not affected by OTC filter settings)
inputs.tooltip: In previous versions of PPA, this feature was not optional and always enabled, however, for some assets it might be useful to disable this option.

inputs.name: Enable mini signals breakouts after Main signal.
inputs.tooltip: Small triangles (triangles are the default shape for mini signals) on the chart showing additional breakouts in the same direction of the Main signal.

inputs.name: Color Bars
inputs.tooltip: When using the 'Classic' color scheme, STRONG GREEN is a STRONG BUY while WEAKER GREEN color is a WEAKENING BUY (Stay cautious from a Sell reversal). STRONG RED is a STRONG SELL while WEAKER RED color is a WEAKENING SELL (Stay cautious from a Buy reversal).

inputs.name: Show All Pivot Breakout Lines
inputs.tooltip: When a price breaks a pivot line, we have a buy or sell signal, and by default, the line is shown as a wide solid line for Main signals and a thin solid line for Mini signals.

inputs.name: Main Signal Pivot Breakout Line width
Mini Signal Pivot Breakout Line width
Show Real Time Pivots transforming (dotted line)
inputs.tooltip: Shows real time high and low pivot transforming lines plotted as dotted lines. This can help you see upcoming breakouts.

inputs.name: Show All Other Historical Pivot Lines (dotted line)
inputs.tooltip: Shows all other historical (non breakouts) pivot lines as dotted lines.

inputs.name: Real Time and historical (non breakout) Pivot Lines width
inputs.tooltip: Line width of real time pivots and historical pivots.

inputs.name: Show False Breakouts Pivot Lines (dashed line)
inputs.tooltip: False breakouts lines (dashed line) are pivot breakouts that happen but do not hold to trigger Buy or Sell signals (applies for Main and Mini signals). For example, Candle High touches an upper pivot line, but does not close above the pivot line, we get a false breakout. These False pivot breakouts are shown by Dashed Line. Additionally, false breakout can happen if OTC NoiseFilter filtered (ignored) a pivot breakout.

inputs.name: Show Pivot Price Label
inputs.tooltip: Shows the pivot breakouts price with labels for Main and/or Mini Signals.

inputs.name: Show Pivot Bands
inputs.tooltip: Show two continual lines, one for High pivots and one for Low pivots.

inputs.name: Stop Loss Type
inputs.tooltip:
Set the stop loss type, 'Fixed' will set a percentage fixed stop loss from the position entry price.
'Trailing percentage' will keep distance between close and 'Maximum percentage loss' parameter, allowing to capture profit.
'Trailing percentage (Auto s/l)' same as latter, but the 'Maximum percentage loss' value is adjusted automatically (manual value will be ignored) based on asset average velocity settings (see 'Auto Stop Loss Settings').
'Trailing SAR' will trail close price based on SAR rules, you can adjust SAR parameters in PPA.
'Trailing Pivot' will track high or low pivot lines following the direction of the position (high pivot for Long and low pivots for short), will also use 'Maximum percentage loss' parameter to give an additional distance.
Note that if '(Auto s/l)' present in stop loss name, 'Maximum percentage loss' will ignored as it will be set automatically by algo (see 'Auto Stop Loss Settings').

inputs.name: Maximum percentage loss - (ignored on 'Auto s/l')
inputs.tooltip: Set the maximum percentage of loss that can be incurred on a trade. For 'Trailing' stop losses types, if the asset price rises or falls in your favor, the stop price moves with it. If the asset price rises or falls against you, the stop stays in place (unless 'Differential percentage reduction' is enabled). NOTE: If the stop loss has a prefix of '(Auto s/l)' on his name, the stop loss value is adjusted automatically and this parameter 'Maximum percentage loss' is ignored.

inputs.name: Close position on touching stop loss. (Real time only)
inputs.tooltip: Enabling this option will close position when touching stop loss, otherwise, (if disabled), wait for candle close to confirm stop loss.

inputs.name: Set percentage reduction value per candle (for all besides SAR, 0 to disable)
inputs.tooltip: Starting from the second candle, after entering a position, this percentage value is reduced from the 'Maximum percentage loss' value or from the 'auto s/l' value in case stop loss value is set automatically. The reduction happens at every candle only when your position goes favorably (winning direction), otherwise, reduction won't occur. Targeted only for 'trailing' stop losses types (besides SAR). Reduction occurs until (stops) reaching minimal value that is set automatically by PPA algo. Set 0 to disable reduction.

inputs.name: Differential percentage reduction even if position price does not go in favor (trailing percentage only)
inputs.tooltip:
For 'trailing percentage' stop loss only.
Works only if 'Set percentage reduction value per candle' is active (value above 0). This will auto reduce 'Maximum percentage loss ' value even if the price goes opposite direction from current entry position. This is calculated by the differential percentage of the 'Maximum percentage loss' value between two candles (small percentage per candle).

inputs.name: max
inputs.tooltip:
START: Start from this value.
STEP: Increase by this value each time an extreme point makes a new high or low.
MAX: Stop increment when reaching this value.

inputs.name: as
inputs.tooltip:
'Percent to s/l' display the percentage between the stop loss and current price (close).
's/l price' displays the price of the stop loss.
'Extra percent' displays an additional percentage value important for calculations, value is determined based on stop loss type (see the documentation for more info).

inputs.name: Alerts will also execute upon stop loss trigger
inputs.tooltip:
In addition to normal buy and sell signals, alerts will also execute when stop-loss triggers. Value of '3' will be executed when stop-loss triggers on LONG positions and '-3' on a SHORT position.
Note that alert named 'STOP LOSS EXECUTED' will NOT be affected by this setting.

inputs.group: Auto Stop Loss Settings (Auto s/l only)
inputs.name: Auto Stop Loss Type
inputs.tooltip:
'Historical Velocity': Set starting 'Maximum percentage loss' percentage based on historical velocity measured from X days by specified time range.
'Current Velocity': Set starting 'Maximum percentage loss' percentage based on current velocity based on X bars.

inputs.group: Auto Stop Loss Settings (Auto s/l only)
inputs.name:
Look back X days OR bars. For 'Historical Velocity' X days.
For 'Current Velocity' X Bars.
inputs.tooltip:
'Historical Velocity': How many DAYS to look back to measure average velocity from bars only in specified time range.
'Current Velocity': How many BARS to look back for current velocity (Time Range is NOT used).

inputs.group: Auto Stop Loss Settings (Auto s/l only)
inputs.name: Time Range for velocity measurement. (Historical Velocity only)
inputs.tooltip: Used determinate average velocity for last X days for this time range only. For 'Historical Velocity' only.

inputs.group: Auto Stop Loss Settings (Auto s/l only)
inputs.name: Velocity multiplier for 'Trailing Percentage' and 'Trailing Pivot' with '(Auto s/l)' only. (1 - no effect)
inputs.tooltip:
This parameter will give you more control over 'Trailing Pivot (Auto s/l)' and 'Trailing Percentage (Auto s/l)', by allowing you to multiply the result of the auto-stop loss value with this multiplier value.
Settings this value to 1 will not affect the 'Auto s/l' value.
Any value above 1 will multiply with the auto-detected stop loss value and increase its value.
Any value below 1 will multiply with the auto-detected stop loss value and decrease its value.
Example: If the multiplier is set to 1.2 the auto-detected stop loss value will multiply by 1.2 which means a 20% constant increment while setting the multiplier to 0.7 the auto-detected stop loss value will multiply by 0.7 which means a 30% constant decrease in auto-detected stop loss.

inputs.name: Use an external indicator for additional signal filtering
External indicator connection for filtering
inputs.tooltip: Use an additional external indicator to filter signals such as DTrendmeter which PPA users receive in the algo pack.
